<br>
You dont need to be near the bridge for these - its very scary the few times I wound up around there (because I got lost in the @#$%ing fog).  Here's where I was - much safer.<br>
<br>
From the Dragon ring, run straight down to the shore.  Turn right and run a long the shore until your SECOND group of iceburgs.  The center iceburg here is your camp spot (any of them actually, I just picked the center one).  From the iceburg there is a gentle slope up - you will usually find your first wolf here - with woods to your right and left.  Wolves are found in the trees.  I would pull one from the trees to my right, then start circling to the left and down the hill - usually by the time I got down the hill, I had all 4 wolves.  Once you get through the trees, you will find yourself in a shallow gorge that opens up into a HUGELY large flat plain (goes almost all the way to the bridge) that only has one giant or two roaming on it...easily avoidable, plenty of room to run circles, do resnares and all that.  At the beginning, I would be finishing my kites within sight of the Bridge, but as I got used to it I found myself doubling back after the second BoF - that way I was almost all the way back to the Medding Iceburg (no wandering mobs) when kite was finished.<br>
<br>
As I mentioned in another thread, I found the experience here to be FAR faster than fighting for Ulthorks if for no other reason that there is hardly anyone on that iceburg (there are about 10-12 spawns in that area, too).<br>
<br>
I will follow up later this evening with the /loc of the iceburg.  Unless you just GOTTA have the tusks and a few pp, this is where you should go first.  I went from frehsly dinged 42 to freshly dinged 44 here in 9 hours - taking occasional time out to port guildies, buy/make food, etc. <p>Skitzolious T. F. Elentaari [Fantasy] <br>
41st Season Wizard - Vaz Server<br>
